  "tour": [
    {
      "order": 1,
      "title": "Start in Bootstrap",
      "description": "Begin with the root app entry point to see how the Flutter bindings, provider stack, and animated shell are assembled. This establishes the top-level structure before you dive into the state and data layers that drive the screens.",
      "nodeIds": [
        "file:lib/main.dart",
        "class:lib/main.dart:NineNineNineApp",
        "class:lib/main.dart:AppShell",
        "function:lib/main.dart:main"
      ],
      "languageLesson": "Flutter apps often use provider composition at the root so navigation and theme changes stay outside the widget tree itself."
    },
    {
      "order": 2,
      "title": "Follow App State",
      "description": "The navigation and theme providers define the app\u2019s moving parts: which screen is visible, which genre is active, and what palette should be used. Understanding this layer makes the later UI files much easier to read because they mostly react to provider state.",
      "nodeIds": [
        "file:lib/providers/navigation_provider.dart",
